snippet.textDisplay:
There's a German poem that sounds so familiar to this, and it's beautiful. It goes like this
"Ich lebe mein Leben in wachsenden Ringen, die sich über die Dinge ziehn. Ich werde den letzten vielleicht nicht vollbringen, aber versuchen will ich ihn."

Which roughly translates to:

"I live my life in ever-widening circles
that stretch themselves out over all the things.
I won't, perhaps, complete the last one,
but I intend on trying."
Rainer Maria Rilke

Via https://lyricstranslate.com

Rip beautiful soul. You've given us such a wonderful gift, I hope you feel all the love in heaven. ♥

snippet.textDisplay: I listened at midnight as soon as it came out, and I loved it, but I didn’t cry like I was certain I would. I have been a Mac fanatic since middle school, and bawled to songs off swimming as recent as 2 weeks ago, but here I am at 6 am after listening to the whole thing front to back again and I’ve not been able to turn the tears off since. I guess I got lost in the new music and it was like he never left, but the harsh reality is setting in as hard as it can right now. I’d really just like to say to anybody reading this, regardless of when you became a fan of Macs or even if you’re not, I hope today is a great day filled with joy, somebody loves you, I love you. Stay safe
